          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1679486320827-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1679486320827-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>halved green chilli[es]</strong> to the pan (can't handle the heat? Just add half!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>tomatoes </strong>into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1679486330538-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1679486330538-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1679486330538-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1679486330538-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1679486330538-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger</strong> (save the matchsticks for later!),<strong> curry powder </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato stock </strong>and<strong> chopped tomatoes </strong>to the pan</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook for 6-8 min or until sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>curry</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't worry if it's a little thick, karahi is drier than most curries!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1679486335425-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1679486335425-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1679486335425-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1679486335425-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1679486335425-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, add the <strong>toasted coconut & almonds</strong> and<strong> half </strong>the<strong> chopped coriander </strong>to the rice and give everything a good mix up<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>peshwari rice</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>cooked paneer</strong> and the<strong> remaining chopped coriander</strong> to the curry and cook for a further 30 secs – this is your <strong>spicy karahi-style paneer</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1679486340528-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
